&lt;h3&gt;Tisha b&#039;Av (begins at sundown)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;General Notes&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before sunset, eat a s&#039;udah mafseket. There is a custom to eat no more than one cooked item.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a twenty-five hour fast. The fast begins at sundown.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Ma&#039;ariv&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We recite a weekday Ma&#039;ariv service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After the Amidah, chant Eicha and Kinot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Traditionally, the lights of the synagogue are dimmed for this part of the service, and the congregation sits in low seats or on the floor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The end of Eicha is chanted as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- The congregation chants 5:21 with the reader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- The reader chants 5:22&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- The congregation chants 5:21&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- The reader repeats 5:21&lt;/p&gt;
